# Creating a NEW GitHub repo: the capability that taught us the most.
#
# In a Claude Code cloud session this fails for TWO independent, stacking reasons.
# Fixing either one alone changes nothing, which is why it took three attempts to
# describe correctly. This descriptor exists so an agent stops rediscovering it.
#
#   1. CREDENTIAL TYPE. The built-in GitHub tools authenticate as the Claude
#      GitHub App. An App installation token cannot create a user-owned repo:
#      POST /user/repos takes a user OAuth token or a PAT. -> 403 "Resource not
#      accessible by integration".
#
#   2. EGRESS POLICY (the wall behind the wall). The session's agent proxy
#      re-terminates TLS and enforces an AUTHORIZED REPOSITORY SET: the repos
#      configured as that session's sources. It refuses GitHub API paths outside
#      that set, and it refuses to inject a credential for them. This holds EVEN
#      IF YOU SUPPLY YOUR OWN VALID PAT: the proxy intercepts the call before
#      GitHub can validate it. Adding GH_TOKEN to the cloud environment does NOT
#      work. Neither does creating the repo in the web UI and pushing into it,
#      because that repo is still outside the authorized set.
#
# So api.github.com answers 200, the credential is correct, and the call remains
# impossible. Host-level reachability does not imply path-level reachability.
#
# THE ESCAPE that does exist: MCP connector traffic is routed through Anthropic's
# servers, NOT through the VM's egress proxy. A user-authenticated GitHub MCP
# connector (github's official remote server, OAuth scope repo) therefore sidesteps
# both walls at once: a user credential, on a channel the proxy never sees. This is
# the same channel that lets the Vercel MCP deploy from a fully locked-down VM.
#
# Verified empirically 2026-07-14 + anthropics/claude-code#76248.

Capability github.repo-create
  Description Create a NEW GitHub repository (needs a user credential AND a path the egress proxy does not filter)
  Probe env GH_TOKEN
  Probe env GITHUB_TOKEN
  Probe file ~/.config/gh/hosts.yml
  Unless env CLAUDE_CODE_REMOTE
  Blocked Cloud session: the agent proxy enforces an authorized repository set and refuses GitHub API calls outside it, even with your own valid PAT. A token in the environment does NOT fix this, and neither does pre-creating the repo in the UI (pushing to it is blocked too). Create it from a local session, or go through a user-authenticated GitHub MCP connector, whose traffic routes via Anthropic and never touches this proxy.
  Requires A user credential (PAT or user OAuth; an App installation token is never enough for user-owned repos) AND an egress path that is not filtered to an authorized repo set.
  Remediation Best from cloud: add github's official remote MCP server (https://api.githubcopilot.com/mcp/) as a custom connector authenticated by OAuth with the repo scope, and call its create_repository. Connector traffic routes through Anthropic and bypasses the VM proxy entirely. Otherwise: create the repo from a LOCAL session (simplest, works today), or delegate to GitHub Actions (a workflow holding a PAT in Actions secrets runs on GitHub infrastructure, where no proxy applies). Do NOT put a PAT in the cloud environment: it is blocked by the proxy and there is no secrets store.
  Risk high
  Environments local

Capability github.repo-write
  Description Read and write repos that are in THIS session's authorized set (issues, PRs, comments, pushes)
  Probe http https://api.github.com
  Requires The Claude GitHub App connection or a synced gh token, AND the target repo must be one of this session's configured sources.
  Remediation Works on the default Trusted network level for the repos this session was opened against. For a repo OUTSIDE that set, the proxy refuses the write and will not inject a credential, no matter which token you hold: open a session whose sources include that repo, or act on it from a local session. Acting on the repo you are bound to is fine; reaching a different one is not.
  Risk low
  Environments local cloud ci
